## Comparativos Duais (A vs B)

Usar variáveis canónicas com fallbacks:

- **Lado A:** `accent: "var(--brand-action, #7c3aed)"`, `bg: "color-mix(in srgb, var(--brand-action, #7c3aed) 10%, transparent)"`, `border: "color-mix(in srgb, var(--brand-action, #7c3aed) 35%, transparent)"`
- **Lado B:** `accent: "var(--brand-contrast, #1e36f8)"`, `bg: "color-mix(in srgb, var(--brand-contrast, #1e36f8) 10%, transparent)"`, `border: "color-mix(in srgb, var(--brand-contrast, #1e36f8) 35%, transparent)"`
- **Badge VS:** `border: "color-mix(in srgb, var(--brand-action, #7c3aed) 35%, transparent)"`, `background: "color-mix(in srgb, var(--brand-action, #7c3aed) 10%, transparent)"`, `color: "var(--brand-action, #7c3aed)"`, `fontSize: 12`, `fontWeight: 800`
- Divider vertical: `width: 1`, `background: t.cardBorder`, `flexShrink: 0`
- Classes `app-conversao-vs-row` e `app-conversao-funil-duo` onde já existem no CSS.

